@startuml
title Meta-Software Generator Workflow

actor "Student / Developer" as Student
participant "Task1 Notebook" as Notebook
participant "Prompt Templates" as Prompts
participant "APIFree / DeepSeek" as AI
participant "Generated Flask Project" as Project
participant "Docs + UML Files" as Docs
participant "Tests + CI Config" as QA

Student -> Notebook : enter healthcare business problem
Notebook -> Prompts : build generation prompts
Prompts -> AI : request requirements, UML, code, tests
AI --> Notebook : generated artifacts

Notebook -> Project : write app.py, templates, static files
Notebook -> Docs : write requirements, safety policy, PlantUML
Notebook -> QA : write pytest files and workflow evidence

Student -> Project : review generated system
Student -> Docs : inspect generated documentation and diagrams
Student -> QA : run tests and CI/CD checks

note over Notebook,QA
This diagram models the software-outside view:
the notebook-driven meta-software process that
generates the assessed Flask website and evidence.
end note
@enduml
